commitResults.messageBody: Resolved DeleteItemCommandParserTest errors.

In process of Unittesting, dificulty was encountered from utilising
testing utilities of original code base.

Specifically the assertCommandSuccess testutil method, relies on the .equals
of model manager, and model manager equality has null values initialised for AB3
and Inventoryinator versions, which if implemented to check, cause testcase
failures in stubs.

Recommended to perform refactor to code base and remove ab3 artifacts, for more effective
testing.

commitResults.messageBody:
ID will now monotonically increase for both recipes and item ids.

Resolve Duplicate ID bug.

Slight "issue" which is improbable in real usecase,
but theoraticaly possible is that an user inputs
addi -n asdf to Integer.MAX_VALUE - 1,

This is because first instance will create the item, but then second onwards will
increase id counter.

then add a new item.

addi -n IKillInventory

Then, exit the program.

Then enter the program

addi -n NowDie

will cause integer overflow, and ID will be negative, causing an error
in ID
